description: A large bird of prey swoops down towards a stork carrying a bundled baby. The predator ironically asks the stork if it would like to contribute to an endangered species, implying the baby would serve as sustenance for its own presumably rare kind. This situation subverts the typical image of a stork delivering life, placing the baby in immediate peril from a predator attempting to justify its hunt with a twisted conservation argument. The scene is absurd and darkly humorous, playing on the concepts of predation and species preservation in a surreal encounter.
caption: “Say ... would you like to contribute to an endangered species?”
